{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771347085,"nonce":"nsvwdpB27jxf32gJiaTFQJTIrd8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rqPOa","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/219","origin":"github"},"title":"Add per-project AGENTS.md convention for agent onboarding","message":"## Feature Request\n\nAgents start cold every session with no knowledge of project repo internals. The workspace\nhas good generic guidance (`.agent/knowledge/`) and architecture docs for the workspace\nitself, but nothing standardized tells agents what packages a project repo contains, where\nthe key files are, or what the common pitfalls are.\n\n### Proposed solution\n\n1. Create a template (`.agent/templates/project_agents_guide.md`) for `AGENTS.md` files\n   that live at the root of each project repo (e.g., `unh_marine_autonomy/AGENTS.md`).\n   Sections: Package Inventory, Repository Layout, Architecture Overview, Key Files to\n   Read First, Build \u0026 Test, Cross-Layer Dependencies, Common Pitfalls.\n\n2. Update all instruction files to tell agents: when entering a project repo, read\n   `AGENTS.md` if it exists.\n\n### Scope\n\n- Template creation and instruction file updates only (workspace repo)\n- Actually populating `AGENTS.md` in each project repo would be separate follow-up issues\n  in those repos\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}